  "id": "TV03",
  "title": "Hash Chain Verification",
  "description": "Hash chain verification vectors: a valid 5-op chain from one device with correct prevHash and currentHash values, and a tampered variant where one payload is modified and the chain breaks. All SHA-256 hashes are computed per the formula: currentHash = SHA256(bytes(prevHash) + base64Decode(encryptedPayload)). In v2, the hash chain uses 'prevHash' (renamed from v1's 'devicePrevHash') and operates over ciphertext bytes, allowing the server to verify integrity without decrypting.",
